## Part 3: Kill Chain Engine Modularization Plan

### kill_chain_engine.py Audit (484 lines)

#### Hardcoded Values to Extract

| Location | Value | Problem |
|---|---|---|
| `_fetch_dark_pool` L189 | `"SPY"` | Only scans SPY |
| `_fetch_cot` L212-213 | `"ES"` | Only scans E-mini S&P |
| `_fetch_gex` L232 | `"SPX"` | Only scans SPX |
| `_fetch_13f` L260 | `["Bridgewater", "Soros", "Berkshire"]` | Fixed fund list |
| `_fetch_dark_pool` L190 | `limit=5` | Fixed top-N count |
| `_fetch_gex` L241-245 | `[:5]`, `[:3]` | Fixed wall/zone limits |
| `__init__` L148 | `cache_ttl=300` | Hardcoded TTL |
| `__init__` L151 | `cache_ttl=3600` | Hardcoded TTL |
| `_detect_mismatches` L334 | `-100000` | Specs "heavy short" threshold |
| `_detect_mismatches` L353 | `20e9` | DP "heavy" threshold ($20B) |
| `_detect_mismatches` L383 | `50` | Short volume % threshold |

#### DRY Violations

1. **Import fallback boilerplate** (lines 30-91): Same try/except + fallback import pattern copied 5 times
2. **Fetcher guard pattern**: Every `_fetch_*` starts with identical null check + try/except
3. **Narrative key stripping**: Done in engine (L481) AND API (L60) — duplicated
4. **Layer name list**: Hardcoded as `["fedwatch","dark_pool","cot","gex","sec_13f"]` in 4+ locations

#### Scalability Gaps

1. Sequential fetching — all 5 layers run one-by-one
2. No scan-level cache — every `/killchain/scan` hits all 5 APIs fresh
3. No per-layer timeout — one slow layer blocks full scan
4. No symbol parameterization — can't scan AAPL/QQQ, only SPY/SPX/ES
5. Mismatch rules hardcoded — adding new rules requires engine edits

